dy/20230902_wof405.png 1280w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 640px, 95vw" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></span></figure><p class="article__body-text">乌克兰于 6 月 4 日正式开始的反攻并未辜负人们的高度期望。到目前为止，只取得了很小的领土收益。然而，近三个月过去了，有迹象表明事情可能会加速。根据美国智库战争研究所（ISW）的地图，自6月5日以来，乌克兰已收复108平方公里的被占领土。自 8 月 22 日以来，乌克兰军队已占领其中约 38 平方公里的土地。这只是俄罗斯手中剩余的10万多平方公里土地中的一小部分。但加速带来了希望。</p><figure> <span itemscope="" itemprop="image" itemtype="https://schema.org/ImageObject" data-slim="0"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://www.economist.com/img/b/1280/2294/90/sites/default/files/images/2021/12/articles/body/20230902_wof911.png"><img loading="lazy" src="https://www.economist.com/img/b/1280/2294/90/sites/default/files/images/2021/12/articles/body/20230902_wof911.png" srcset="https://www.economist.com/img/b/200/358/90/sites/default/files/images/2021/12/articles/body/20230902_wof911.png 200w,https://www.economist.com/img/b/300/538/90/sites/default/files/images/2021/12/articles/body/20230902_wof911.png 300w,https://www.economist.com/img/b/400/717/90/sites/default/files/images/2021/12/articles/body/20230902_wof911.png 400w,https://www.economist.com/img/b/600/1075/90/sites/default/files/images/2021/12/articles/body/20230902_wof911.png 600w,https://www.economist.com/img/b/640/1147/90/sites/default/files/images/2021/12/articles/body/20230902_wof911.png 640w,https://www.economist.com/img/b/800/1434/90/sites/default/files/images/2021/12/articles/body/20230902_wof911.png 800w,https://www.economist.com/img/b/1000/1792/90/sites/default/files/images/2021/12/articles/body/20230902_wof911.png 1000w,https://www.economist.com/img/b/1280/2294/90/sites/default/files/images/2021/12/articles/body/20230902_wof911.png 1280w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 640px, 95vw" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></span></figure><p class="article__body-text"><span>最近来自南部前线的消息也是如此。乌克兰攻击的重点现在似乎集中在扎波罗热市以南。 8 月 28 日，在多条战线经过三个月的艰苦奋战后，乌克兰军队解放了主攻轴线沿线的一个约有 500 人的罗布坦村庄。它的占领意味着乌克兰军队终于到达了所谓的苏罗维金线，即俄罗斯在该地区的主要防御工事线。俄罗斯将其资源集中在第一道防线上（见地图）。这可能会让乌克兰人处于突破的边缘：超过这一点，俄罗斯的防御就会更薄弱，而他们希望的储备也会更薄弱。</span></p> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 04 Sep 2023 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> /内容/phkkqjq2j455o4qf1e279gv5v2r91fj5</guid><link/> https://www.economist.com/espressochart/2023<category>不确定</category><category>联合国</category><category>刚果民主共和国</category><category>埃塞俄比亚</category><category>印度</category><category>尼日利亚</category><category>巴基斯坦</category><category>中国</category><category>人口增长</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Meet Ernie, China’s answer to ChatGPT]]></title><description><![CDATA[<section class="css-1ugvd2u e18wk22u0"><style data-emotion="css qts40t">.css-qts40t img{display:block;}.css-qts40t .edweubf2{margin-top:0.25rem;}</style><figure class="css-qts40t e1197rjj0"><img alt="李彦宏" fetchpriority="high" width="1280" height="720" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color:transparent" sizes="(min-width: 960px) 700px, 95vw" srcset="https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=360,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_WBP504.jpg 360w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=384,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_WBP504.jpg 384w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=480,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_WBP504.jpg 480w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=600,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_WBP504.jpg 600w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=834,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_WBP504.jpg 834w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=960,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_WBP504.jpg 960w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1096,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_WBP504.jpg 1096w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1280,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_WBP504.jpg 1280w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1424,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230902_WBP504.jpg 1424w"